INDIA: Indian Gujarat cotton falls amid sluggish demand.Indian Gujarat cotton falls amid sluggish demand.Indian Gujarat cotton varieties extended losses on Tuesday on sluggish demand and fresh offerings by stockists and state agencies, dealers said.Punjab cotton was steady, they said.In spot deals Gujarat Kalyan (medium staple) fell by 200/300 rupees to 11,800/12,000 rupees per candy (355.56 kg) while wagad cotton fell by 100/200 to 10,300/10,400.Punjab was quiet on limited activity. Punjab saw-ginned was steady at 1,675/1,700 rupees per maund (37.32 kg) while F-414 was quiet at 1,925/1,940. "About 1,400/1,500 bales (170 kg each) of Punjab cotton were traded today," one broker said.-- Bombay Commodities +91-22-265 9000